    <!-- Panel 1: Selling & Transactions -->
    <div class="captab-panel active" id="cap-selling" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="pillars-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px;">
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-device-mobile"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Mobile-first POS</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Full-featured POS on iPhone or iPad. Untether associates from the cash wrap — sell from the fitting room, the stockroom, or the sales floor. Purpose-built for a native iOS experience.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-credit-card"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Flexible payments</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Tap to Pay on iPhone, Apple Pay, contactless, chip, and swipe. Supports split tenders, mixed carts, gift cards, and Buy Now Pay Later. Platform-agnostic: Adyen, Stripe, PayPal, Clover — your choice, no penalties.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-calculator"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Promotions & loyalty</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">One unified engine for tier-discounts, percentage/fixed promotions, loyalty rewards, coupon stacking rules, and tax exemptions. Same logic across POS, e-commerce, and mobile — no pricing discrepancies.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Panel 2: Inventory & Fulfillment -->
    <div class="captab-panel" id="cap-inventory" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="pillars-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px;">
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-package"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Real-time inventory</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Item-level visibility across every store, warehouse, and channel. Receiving, transfers, cycle counts, and adjustments — all from the iOS device. RFID-powered counts take minutes, not days.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-shopping-bag"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Endless Aisle & Save the Sale</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Size 11 out of stock? Ship from another store or warehouse in 3 taps. Capture every sale with enterprise-wide inventory access. Footwear brands see 15–22% revenue lift from integrated Endless Aisle.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-truck-delivery"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">BOPIS & ship-from-store</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Buy Online Pick Up In Store, curbside, ship-from-store, and Buy Online Return In Store (BORIS). Turn every location into a micro-fulfillment center with guided associate workflows and smart order routing.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Panel 3: Customer & Operations -->
    <div class="captab-panel" id="cap-customer" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="pillars-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px;">
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-heart-handshake"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Clienteling & CRM</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">360° customer profiles with purchase history, preferences, wishlists, and notes — across every channel. Store-to-door messaging lets associates send lookbooks and personalized outreach directly from the POS.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-arrows-exchange"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Returns & exchanges</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Cross-channel returns and exchanges with no sync lag. Return an online order in-store and have that inventory immediately available for the next walk-in. Receipt lookup, refund to original tender, or store credit.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-lock-access"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Cash & operations</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Drawer memos, blind counts, variance alerts, safe-control checklists, and digital receipting. Pre-flight routines ensure cash consistency at open and close. Paperless workflows reduce waste and speed up handoffs.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Panel 4: Identity & Loyalty -->
    <div class="captab-panel" id="cap-identity" role="tabpanel">
      <div class="pillars-grid" style="grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 12px;">
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-scan-eye"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">Facial recognition login</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Associate login powered by Amazon Rekognition, not device-bound Face ID. Any associate can authenticate on any register — recognition follows the person, not the hardware — for faster login and tighter security.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-qrcode"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">QR loyalty sign-up</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Customers scan a QR code at the register — or anywhere in the store — to enroll in loyalty themselves. No verbal info exchange, no manual entry errors, and a real lift in sign-up volume you can market to.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="pillar-card pillar-card-compact">
          <div class="pillar-icon"><i class="ti ti-login"></i></div>
          <h3 class="pillar-title">QR associate login</h3>
          <p class="pillar-desc">Rotating QR-code sign-in for associates — fast, secure authentication at the register with nothing to type.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

